HEADWORD: Aorist
<hw>A"o*rist</hw> <pr>(⟦amac⟧"⟦osl⟧*r⟦icr⟧st)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>'ao`ristos</grk> indefinite; <grk>'a</grk> priv. +
<grk>"ori`zein</grk> to define, <?/ boundary, limit.]</ety>
<fld>(Gram.)</fld> <def>A tense in the Greek language, which expresses
an action as completed in past time, but leaves it, in other respects,
wholly indeterminate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aoristic</ent>⟦br⟧
